        <p>
            Stadskwekerij De Kas is a residents' initiative by Eva Bes and Marja Versteeg, two gardeners from North Rotterdam with a heart for nature and people. Together with all our volunteers, we are committed to improving the city's biodiversity and the connection between people and organizations.

            The location of the Stadskwekerij De Kas is a greenhouse complex in the heart of Rotterdam. It consists of a sustainable nursery with an inspiration garden. In 2020 the demand for our pesticide-free plants grew. We were frustrated that we could not meet this demand due to lack of space and time. At the same time, more and more residents spontaneously offered us their seedlings and cuttings. Then the idea quickly arose to develop a digital platform where we can meet supply and demand. Students of the Rotterdam University of Applied Sciences came to our rescue and so BiodiverCityMAX was born

            BiodiverCityMAX offers a platform on which all plant enthusiasts can share plants and knowledge with each other. This way, we form one large sustainable nursery that is committed to a non-toxic, affordable and green world.
        </p>

